{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Filling","content":["Place a bowl on mixing bowl lid and weigh in oats. Remove then cover with water and set aside.","Place cashews in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl.","Place parsley in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>2 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Transfer to bowl with cashews and set aside.","Place onions, tomatoes, peppers, oil, garlic and 1 tsp salt in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then sauté <nobr>5 min\/120°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Meanwhile, drain oats and discard water.","Add well-drained oats and cook <nobr>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add eggs and stir in with spatula then cook <nobr>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add reserved cashews and parsley, remaining 1 tsp salt and oregano then mix together with spatula. Transfer to a bowl and set aside to cool. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl and make dough."]},{"title":"Dough","content":["Place water and salt in mixing bowl. Insert simmering basket and weigh in potatoes then cook <nobr>25 min\/100°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula. Discard steaming water.","Place cooked potatoes and butter in mixing bowl then mash <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add flour and whisk <nobr>1 min\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Tip out, wrap in cling film and set aside for 20 minutes. Meanwhile, preheat oven to 180°C and line 3 baking trays with baking paper.","On a floured surface, roll out dough (see tip). Using a pastry cutter (approx. Ø 9 cm) cut out 80 circles, re-rolling any trimmings (see tip). Place 1 tsp cooled filling in one half of each circle, then fold over into a half-moon and seal by pinching pastry edges together.","Place pasties on prepared trays, brush with beaten egg yolks and bake for 25 minutes (180°C). Serve hot or cold."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Filling","content":["150 g rolled oats","water, for soaking","100 g cashew nuts","15 g fresh parsley","150 g onions, quartered","250 g tinned chopped tomatoes","50 g red peppers, cut in pieces","50 g olive oil","4 garlic cloves","2 tsp fine sea salt","3 large eggs","1 tsp dried oregano"]},{"title":"Dough","content":["800 g water","1 tsp fine sea salt","600 g potatoes, red skin, peeled, cut in pieces (2 cm)","240 g unsalted butter, soft","600 g strong white bread flour, plus extra for dusting","3 egg yolks, beaten, for brushing"]}],"id":"r134380","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-vSk5A4x8onA\/XZam1xUt5tI\/AAAAAAAAg2U\/rP3l5vrDYlE5y3DCg4oZlu2jMuvVC6iYwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_-3fqNdAQX20aVzbx.png","title":"Oat and Cashew Pasties","publishedAt":"2018-02-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2 g","fat":"4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"9 g","calories":"343 kJ \/ 82 kcal"},"usefulItems":"medium mesh sieve, cling film, baking trays and baking paper, rolling pin, pastry brush, round pastry cutter (Ø 9 cm), oven","hintsAndTricks":["The cashew nuts can be replaced with walnuts, pine nuts or toasted hazelnuts.","Vary the filling as desired.","When cutting dough circles, divide dough into <nobr>8 pieces<\/nobr> (keeping remaining dough covered under cling film) and roll out each piece to <nobr>1-2 mm<\/nobr> thick. Cut <nobr>10 circles<\/nobr> from each dough piece, re-rolling as necessary.","If oven space is limited or only <nobr>1-2 baking<\/nobr> trays are available, cook in batches. Prepare pasties, place on baking paper, then slide onto a baking tray when one becomes available. Remove hot pasties to a wire rack once cooked."],"basicInfo":["medium","1h","2h 30m","80 pieces"]}